The time has come to tear down our bedroom. The last room in the house where nothing has been done, just a little decoration.
Remove the horrible electric fireplace and the hearth. Frame the chimney, replace the damaged plaster and sand it. Make a custom closet.
We always start with a quick sketch in pencil...
The dirty step is done.
I found several dead birds at the back of the chimney; all completely dried out :(
Ready for the plasterer next week
Happy with the small niche on the side
Insert the new closet here (it's not like we've already started drawing it 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the radiator!
And we even thought of adding a lovely little vent to prevent the chimney from getting damp
The chimney sweep took care of installing the cap and the draft stop. It should be a bit safer for the birds nesting up there 🪺
The plasterer is done. We're installing the floor tomorrow!
The wood shavings underlayer is in place, I improvised a wood shavings extractor with a roll of toilet paper as an attachment for the vacuum 😂
Some of the planks are sorted and ready to install. We're just taking a tea break
Well, progress was slow today because of super delicate cuts around the door posts to achieve a smooth transition into the hallway (which is also being installed). @user45@twitter.com cursed me
Done, but on my knees! Cherry on top: the incomprehensible instructions for assembling the new bed. We'll sleep well tonight!
The hallway floor and all the skirtings remain to be done. The decorator is coming in a month, so in the meantime, at home, it's the chic of plaster without primer.
Little DIY session this evening to remove the lower sections of the door posts with the miter saw/scissors where we want the floor to be perfectly fitted.
The wood shavings underlayer of the hallway is also in place
We finished the hallway floor yesterday! Then off at 5 am this morning to pick up Thing 1 from Heathrow, then a nap and the final stretch for the hallway; skirtings installed. We'll deal with the insulation once the adhesive has set.
